.SH NAME
CWE\-416 \- Use After Free
.SH RANK
2025 CWE Top 25 rank: \fB#7\fR (2024 rank: 8).
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: Memory Safety.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Memory is referenced after being freed. The freed block may be reallocated for another purpose, so the dangling pointer aliases unrelated data; results range from crashes to information disclosure to attacker\-controlled execution. A C/C++ manual\-memory weakness.
.SH MITIGATION
Null out pointers after free, establish clear ownership, and avoid multiple aliases to freed memory. Use AddressSanitizer/Valgrind; in C++ use smart pointers; consider Rust where its ownership model prevents the class.
